folder: Nassau Street & Pine Street, Manhattan, NY
text:
An aerial view of Nassau Sgreet, at, adjoining and north of the N.E. corner of Pine Street, showing demolition of the Hanover National Bank Building.
June 25, 1931.
P. L. Sperr.

folder: Pine Street & Nassau Street, Manhattan, NY
text:
(1)
Pine Street, south side, east from and including Nassau Street. The view shows the United States Sub-Treasury on the S.E. corner
of Pine and Nassau Streets.
August 24, 1929.
P. L. Sperr.
(2)
The same, from a different angle, at a later date, showing the lower part of the new Bank of Manhattan Building.
September 26, 1931.
P. L. Sperr.
(3)
The same, showing complete structure of the Bank of Manhattan
Building.
July 26, 1931.
P. L. Sperr.

folder: Nassau Street & Pine Street, Manhattan, NY
text:
(1)
Nassau Street, east side, south from and including Pine Street, showing the United States Sub-Treasury Building. (Nassau Street, is a continuation of Broad Street, at this point. Shown in the foreground is Pine Street, south side, at Nassau Street. Excavation shown at the S.W. corner is for an addition to the Bankers Trust Building (14 Wall Street).

September 16, 1931.
P. L. Sperr.

(2)
The same, from a different angle.
July 26, 1931.
P. L. Sperr.
